// conversations.storyarc
// part of Arcturus, a programming language and compiler for the Infocom Z-machine.
// Copyright (c) 2026, Stefan Vogt.
// https://github.com/ByteProject/Arcturus
//
// A showcase for the conversations granule: the menu presentation of the `topic`
// model. TALK TO a person and their topics in view are listed as a numbered menu,
// held static in the upper window while the conversation scrolls below; press the
// number to ask one. It is summoned alongside the statusline (as a real game
// would have it), so the score/room bar sits above the menu - the two coexist.
//
// The same `topic` model drives the typed ask/tell path (see
// infocom-interrogation.storyarc); here it is the menu instead. Note that menu
// topics need no `words`: you pick by number, not by typing a subject, so a
// conversations-only person stays tidy.
//
//   arcc examples/granules/conversations.storyarc -o conversations.z5
//   frotz conversations.z5
//
// Things to try: TALK TO ESME, then 1 (your fortune) - a new line opens. Follow
// it down to her warning, which lands once and then leaves the list. TAKE the
// COIN and talk again: a topic gated on holding it has appeared.

game
    title "The Seer's Tent"
    headline "A Cosmos conversation-menu showcase"
    author "Stefan Vogt"
    start tent

summon.statusline
summon.conversations

room tent
    name "A Seer's Tent"
    desc "Candlelight pools on a round table draped in star-stitched velvet. The
          air is thick with incense, and shadows lean in from the canvas walls."

thing esme of person in tent
    name "Madame Esme"
    named
    words esme, madame, seer, woman

    // reveal grows the menu, `once` and `when` shape it, and you / reply / say
    // read just as on the ask/tell path - the topic model is the same.

    topic fortune "your fortune"
        you "What do you see for me?"
        reply "A long road, and a choice at the end of it you will not want to make."
        reveal road

    topic cards "the tarot cards"
        you "Tell me about these cards of yours."
        reply "They do not foretell. They only show you what you already fear."

    topic road "the long road" hidden
        you "This road. Where does it lead?"
        reply "North, into the dark. You knew that before you sat down."
        reveal warning

    topic warning "her warning" hidden once
        say "She turns a single card and lays it between you. The Tower, inverted."
        reply "When the moment comes, choose the living over the dead. That is all the cards will give."
        change score to score + 1

    topic coin "the silver coin" when player holds coin
        you "What do I owe you for the reading?"
        reply "Leave the coin where it lies. This was paid for in older coin than silver."

thing coin in tent
    name "silver coin"
    words silver, coin
    intro "A silver coin glints at the edge of the table."
    desc "A worn silver coin, cold to the touch."
